The paper deals with designing a space-efficient algorithm for performing depth-first search traversal of a graph, which is a fundamental problem in computer science and falls under the category of data structures (cs.DS) and algorithms (cs.AL). The algorithm also has implications in information theory (cs.IT) as it uses a compressed representation of the graph. Additionally, the paper involves analyzing the time complexity of the algorithm, which is a common theme in computational complexity (cs.CC) and discrete mathematics (cs.DM).
